## Project Content
 - Modular structure to  provide basic building block for any angular 6 project.
 - following files description as follows
    - `Public Module` - used to handle components required before user login.
        - `login` -login component for application.
        - `registration` -registration component for application.
    - `Shared Module` - used to contain all common components & filters required in overall application.
        - `image` -customcomponent to handle images in overall application.
        - `filter` -Angular pipe to filter array list with respect to supplied key and value.
    - `Private Module` - used to handle components required after user login.
        - `sidebar` -created to supply common funciton for http request.
        - `service` -Consist of services required inside private module only. `internal service` - contains all functions to communicate with API service to make Backend calls.
        - `dashboard` -simple landing component to redirect page after user login to go inside appliation.
    - `services` - used to hold services required in overall application consist of `Api,Auth, AuthGuard , Core, Interceptor`.
        - `Api` -created to supply common funciton for http request.
        - `Auth` -created to contain funcitons related to authentication and also holds login logout functionality.
        - `AuthGuard` -created to Apply angular guard for authentication.
        - `Core` -Consist three services `Helper, Constant, Language` helper service to hold common funcitons which can be used in overall application, constants to hold static values in application.
        - `Interceptor` -created to handle authenticaton required to make Http calls it can intercept all http cals to provide authtoken or extract any values before or agter calling server.
    
